==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Predecessor
<hw>Pred`e*ces"sor</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praedecessor</ets>; <ets>prae</ets> before + <ets>decessor</ets>
one who withdraws from the province he has governed, a retiring officer
(with reference to his successor), a predecessor, fr.
<ets>decedere</ets>: cf. F. <ets>pr⟦eacute⟧d⟦eacute⟧cesseur</ets>. See
<er>Decease</er>.]</ety> <def>One who precedes; one who has preceded
another in any state, position, office, etc.; one whom another follows
or comes after, in any office or position.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A prince who was as watchful as his <qex>predecessor</qex> had
been over the interests of the state.</q>
<rj><qau>Prescott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Predeclare</ent>⟦br⟧
